race.comment: AT WITZ END (1) is a veteran who struggles in town these days but has found his right level here. Worked to the line well without threatening last start over 1200m at Doomben. The extra trip looks ideal. Has his share of weight but has earned it. PRANCING WITH FIRE (4) moved into contention on the corner then kept finding to finish second when resuming over 1300m at Ballina last time out. Will enjoy the extra 100m and at the weights poses a serious threat. HE'S A COPY BOY (6) charged home to win the Krambach Cup over the mile at Taree eight days ago when second-up from a spell. Open to further improvement and although back in distance looks a major contender down in the weights. GOBBLED (3) disappointed last start as unplaced favourite in the Tabulam Cup over this distance. Gets a soft run from gate one and can do a lot better. CREDIT CONTROLLER (5) has been about the mark all prep and should be at her peak for this.
